Sentencas: Ce0.8Y0.2O2-delta (YDC) was infiltrated into a BaCo0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-delta (BCFN) cathode of intermediate temperature sold oxide full cells (IT-SOFCs) in order to decrease its cathodic polarization resistance.
Titulo: Decreasing the Polarization Resistance of BaCo0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ Cathodes by Infiltration of Ce0.8Y0.2O2-δ

Sentencas: BCFN and YDC infiltrated BCFN electrodes were fabricated on dense Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-delta (GDC) thin pellets to form symmetrical cells.
Titulo: Decreasing the Polarization Resistance of BaCo0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ Cathodes by Infiltration of Ce0.8Y0.2O2-δ

Sentencas: The electrochemical impedance spectra of the symmetrical cells were investigated in this present study.
Titulo: Decreasing the Polarization Resistance of BaCo0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ Cathodes by Infiltration of Ce0.8Y0.2O2-δ

Sentencas: Firstly, the thickness of BCFN electrodes was optimized, and controlled at 30 mm for further study.
Titulo: Decreasing the Polarization Resistance of BaCo0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ Cathodes by Infiltration of Ce0.8Y0.2O2-δ

Sentencas: The effects of infiltrated YDC amount and firing temperature on electrode polarization resistance were studied.
Titulo: Decreasing the Polarization Resistance of BaCo0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ Cathodes by Infiltration of Ce0.8Y0.2O2-δ

Sentencas: The symmetrical cells infiltrated with 30 mL YDC solution and fired at 900 degrees C exhibited the lowest electrode polarization resistance in all samples.
Titulo: Decreasing the Polarization Resistance of BaCo0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ Cathodes by Infiltration of Ce0.8Y0.2O2-δ

Sentencas: It was suggested that infiltration of YDC resulted in more active sites and prolonged TPBs in electrodes, improving the surface oxygen exchange, and finally improved the electrode performance.
Titulo: Decreasing the Polarization Resistance of BaCo0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ Cathodes by Infiltration of Ce0.8Y0.2O2-δ
